FBIS3-32200 "drlat024_a_94005" FBIS-LAT-94-024 Document Type:Daily Report 4 Feb 1994 Cuba Alarcon: Relations With EU `On Right Track' FL0302161494 Havana Radio Rebelde Network in Spanish 1000 GMT 3 Feb 94 FL0302161494 Havana Radio Rebelde Network Language: Spanish Article Type:BFN [Text] National Assembly President Ricardo Alarcon has expressed his conviction that Cuba's relations with the European Union [EU] are on the right track; he is hoping to conclude a general cooperation agreement with the EU soon. Alarcon is currently visiting Germany. On 2 February, in Bonn, he met with (Hans Klein), vice president of the German Parliament; deputies in charge of relations with Central America and the Caribbean; and representatives of the Christian Democratic Union, headed by Chancellor Helmut Kohl. In statements to the press, Alarcon stressed: Cuba has to make a series of changes in its economy, but it is not seeking to transform the basic elements of its political design, which is socialism.
